Removing an inappropriate "Citation Needed" flag. It asked why vector and scalar quantities were being added in the equation below it. The equation (as stated explicitly in the flagged sentence) is a geometrical algebra equation, and geometrical algebra freely allows the sum and products of scalars and vectors (indeed going further with objects called multivectors), and so the equation is well defined. Given that the sentence explicitly states that it's working in the geometric algebra framework, and links to it, this is not an uncited fact.
